---
// /request-a-review (CHK-7.2) — the real page the Lens's reviewRoute links to (else that link 404s and
// the promise is broken). A STATIC, crawlable Base page. Per the real-promises rule (MEMORY): an
// outward-facing commitment must be REAL and keepable, never invented. So this page is scrupulously
// honest about what nominating a product actually does — it FEEDS SOMNARY'S GRADING BACKLOG — and it
// states plainly that we cannot promise an individual reply or a turnaround time. It invents NO inbox,
// NO SLA, NO "we'll email you back".
//
// A capture FORM is deliberately NOT shipped here: the env-gated Supabase capture pattern (CHK-4.2)
// needs the owner's project + keys, and wiring/self-hiding it is more than trivial — so per the plan
// this ships as the honest static page and the optional form is noted as a 7.3 follow-up. Nothing on
// this page makes a promise the site can't keep today.
//
// CHK-7.3a adds the capture FORM (the 7.2 follow-up noted below): a progressive-enhancement nomination
// form posting to /api/nominate (env-gated Supabase capture, mirrors CHK-4.2). It writes to the SEPARATE,
// firewalled backlog store (review_nominations) — never a grade. The honest real-promises copy is
// UNCHANGED; the form sits under the "what it honestly can't promise" section so the limits are read first.
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import ContextBanner from '../components/ContextBanner.astro';
import ReviewNominateForm from '../components/ReviewNominateForm.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Request a full human review | Somnary"
  description="Nominate a sleep supplement or ingredient for a full human evidence review on Somnary. Nominations feed Somnary's grading backlog and help decide what gets graded next — we can't promise an individual reply or a turnaround time. Educational, not medical advice."
  canonical="https://somnary.vercel.app/request-a-review"
>
  <main class="page">
    <header class="head">
      <p class="eyebrow">Request a review · feed the grading backlog</p>
      <h1 class="title">Nominate a remedy for a full human review</h1>
      <p class="dek">
        Somnary’s grades come from a human reading the published evidence — not from an algorithm and
        not from the Lens. If the Lens researched something the tier board doesn’t cover yet, you can
        nominate it here so a person looks at it for a full graded write-up.
      </p>
    </header>

    <ContextBanner
      note="This is a nomination, not a grade and not a reply. It adds a subject to Somnary's grading backlog — it doesn't return a verdict or a personalised answer."
    />

    <section class="prose" aria-label="What a review request does">
      <h2 class="h2">What nominating a remedy does</h2>
      <p>
        A nomination goes onto Somnary’s <strong>grading backlog</strong> — the running list of
        supplements and ingredients waiting for a full, human, source-first review. What gets graded
        next is decided by that backlog together with what readers are searching for and where the
        evidence is worth the work. Nominating something makes it a candidate; it does not put it at the
        front of the queue.
      </p>

      <h2 class="h2">What it honestly can’t promise</h2>
      <p>
        We want to be straight with you about the limits, because a promise we can’t keep is worse than
        no promise:
      </p>
      <ul class="list">
        <li>We <strong>can’t promise an individual reply.</strong> There is no support inbox behind this page and no “we’ll email you back”.</li>
        <li>We <strong>can’t promise a turnaround time.</strong> There is no service-level guarantee — a full human review is slow, careful work, and some subjects never clear the evidence bar to earn a graded page.</li>
        <li>A nomination is <strong>not medical advice</strong> and not a verdict on whether something works or is safe.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        What we can say honestly: every nomination is read, and the backlog is what the grading work
        draws from.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="nominate" aria-label="Nominate a remedy for review">
      <h2 class="h2">Nominate a remedy</h2>
      <p class="nominate-lead">
        Name the product or ingredient. It joins the grading backlog for a human to weigh — nothing
        here returns a grade, a verdict, or a reply.
      </p>
      <ReviewNominateForm />
    </section>

    <section class="prose" aria-label="What to read now">
      <h2 class="h2">In the meantime</h2>
      <p>
        The evidence that already exists is here now, graded and cited:
      </p>
      <ul class="list">
        <li><a href="/tiers">Browse the graded tier board</a> — every remedy Somnary has reviewed, S–F, on human evidence.</li>
        <li><a href="/lens">Use the Lens</a> to research a product the corpus doesn’t cover yet — it shows what the published evidence does and doesn’t establish.</li>
        <li><a href="/compare">Compare remedies side by side</a>, or check a product’s label with the <a href="/label-checker">label checker</a>.</li>
        <li>If a sleep problem is ongoing or serious, <a href="/when-to-see-a-doctor">see when to talk to a doctor</a> — that deserves a real clinical assessment, not a supplement.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <p class="review-line">
      Reviewed 2026-07-21 · found an error? <a href="/methodology#corrections">corrections →</a>
    </p>
  </main>
</Base>

<style>
  .page {
    max-width: 760px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: var(--sp-8) var(--sp-7) var(--sp-9);
  }
  .eyebrow {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    letter-spacing: var(--tracking-label);
    color: var(--muted);
    margin: 0;
  }
  .head {
    margin-bottom: var(--sp-6);
  }
  .title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: var(--text-3xl);
    line-height: var(--lh-3xl);
    letter-spacing: var(--tracking-tight);
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: var(--sp-3) 0 var(--sp-5);
  }
  .dek {
    font-size: var(--text-md);
    line-height: var(--lh-md);
    color: var(--muted);
    max-width: 64ch;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .prose {
    margin-top: var(--sp-7);
  }
  .h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: var(--text-xl);
    line-height: var(--lh-xl);
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: var(--sp-7) 0 var(--sp-3);
  }
  .prose p {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    line-height: var(--lh-base);
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: 0 0 var(--sp-4);
    max-width: 64ch;
  }
  .list {
    margin: 0 0 var(--sp-4);
    padding: 0;
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--sp-3);
  }
  .list li {
    position: relative;
    padding-left: var(--sp-5);
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    line-height: var(--lh-base);
    color: var(--ink);
    max-width: 64ch;
  }
  .list li::before {
    content: '·';
    position: absolute;
    left: var(--sp-1);
    top: 0;
    color: var(--primary);
    font-weight: 700;
  }
  .prose a {
    color: var(--primary);
  }

  .nominate {
    margin-top: var(--sp-7);
  }
  .nominate-lead {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    line-height: var(--lh-base);
    color: var(--ink);
    max-width: 64ch;
    margin: 0 0 var(--sp-5);
  }

  .review-line {
    margin-top: var(--sp-8);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    letter-spacing: var(--tracking-label);
    color: var(--muted);
  }
  .review-line a {
    color: var(--primary);
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .page {
      padding: var(--sp-6) var(--sp-5) var(--sp-8);
    }
    .title {
      font-size: var(--text-2xl);
    }
  }
</style>
